Content: [dscrd-prt] <jackclark> Hi, transferred ARRR to my SevenSeas wallet.  Later restarted computer and wallet won‚Äôt load.  It‚Äôs stuck on ‚ÄúActivating best chain‚Äù for 30+ minutes.  Can anyone help me know how to get past this and load the wallet?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <jackclark> Running SevenSeas wallet on Windows.  Keeps saying ‚Äúactivating best chain‚Äù and won‚Äôt load further.  Also says ‚Äúno connection‚Äù in lower right corner of wallet.  Was running fine before computer rebooted.  I had a significant ARRR balance on the wallet, and now I can‚Äôt load it.  Is this malware?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content:
[dscrd-prt] <ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢> `Also says ‚Äúno connection‚Äù in lower right corner of wallet... Is this malware?`
Yes, Windows OS is malware; Windows hijacks your control of core computer functions and is stopping your wallet from connecting to other nodes (which is why you cannot get into a synced state)...

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <jackclark> OK, do you know how can I fix this?  Everything had synced previously when I installed the wallet, and I was able to transfer ARRR from an exchange to the wallet.    My firewall is off.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <Bradbury> I don't think you have anything to worry about. Your coins are safe. I do not use SevenSeas but have had issues with the other wallet and I find that if I download the bootstrap (copy the bootstap files to the correct location) it all started working fine again.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <jackclark> Thanks for both of you for you responses.  The wallet just spontaneously connected after an hour or so of not being able to.  Strange, but fortunately now I see my balance.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <Bradbury> might also be worth making a copy of wallet.dat and keeping in a safe location. then delete wallet.dat and restarting the wallet.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <Bradbury> then importing your z address

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <Bradbury> good news

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <jackclark> Yes, I‚Äôll make a copy of wallet.dat.  I notice my z address is gone.  Should I just hit ‚Äúnew address‚Äù?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <Bradbury> if you want to add a current z address then you will need to run the command to import

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <jackclark> OK thank you

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <Bradbury> z_importkey (followed by) secret-extended-key- (then your key)

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-prt] <jackclark> I‚Äôm now seeing the prior z address under transactions.  Thanks so much for your assistance.  Wishing the best for this project.
